issue.title: Add CLAUDE.md for Claude Code guidance
issue.body:
## Description

Add a CLAUDE.md file to provide comprehensive guidance for Claude Code when working with this repository.

## Motivation

When using Claude Code (claude.ai/code) for development on this project, it's helpful to have project-specific guidance that includes:
- Development commands and workflows
- Architecture patterns and design decisions  
- Code style and testing requirements
- Integration points and configuration

This will help ensure consistent development practices and make it easier for AI-assisted coding to follow the project's established patterns.

## Benefits

- Improved consistency when using Claude Code for development
- Clear documentation of development commands and quality checks
- Explicit guidance on the project's DDD and Clean Architecture patterns
- Better onboarding for contributors using AI-assisted development tools

commits.message:
chore: update translations progress (#4780)

Co-authored-by: mergify[bot] <37929162+mergify[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>

Improves Windows build process

Streamlines the Windows build process by enabling long paths, prepping
directories, ensuring Cargo shims are on the PATH, and installing the
Rust toolchain with necessary components and targets. This change simplifies
the build setup and ensures compatibility with dependencies that may
require specific targets. It also sets up the toolchain for a minimal
profile to reduce unnecessary dependencies during the build.

issue.title: Reopen email submission ports

type.name: Feature
type.description: A request, idea, or new functionality

issue.body:
A while ago, we blocked outbound traffic from Zos VMs to certain ports used for email (see https://github.com/threefoldtech/zos/issues/1987).

That was implemented as this firewall rule:

https://github.com/threefoldtech/zos/blob/0199ee83ff9918918f18fd25fd7ba1cdc1c7abce/cmds/modules/networkd/nft.go#L53

This was a success, in the sense that we don't have anymore complaints about Zos nodes sending spam email. On the other hand, we are getting some questions about why VMs aren't able to communicate on ports 465 and 587.

The summary of what the common email ports are used for is as follows:

* 25 - used for sending mail between mail servers (this is the main concern for spam)
* 465 & 587 - used for submitting mail to a mail providers server, with authentication (not really a concern for spam)

Given that, I'd like to propose that we reopen ports 465 and 587. Have also discussed with @delandtj who is in agreement that this should be safe.

---

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>cloudflare/workers-sdk (wrangler)</summary>

### [`v4.30.0`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/blob/HEAD/packages/wrangler/CHANGELOG.md#4300)

[Compare Source](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/compare/wrangler@4.29.1...wrangler@4.30.0)

##### Minor Changes

- [#​10341](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10341) [`76a6701`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/76a6701fd5dc2d8493ad28a0ba8e79530885c05e) Thanks [@​garvit-gupta](https://redirect.github.com/garvit-gupta)! - feat: Add Wrangler command for Vectorize list-vectors operation

##### Patch Changes

- [#​10217](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10217) [`979984b`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/979984b8dfd3bc5d18c2aeedc4850da8c41d0476) Thanks [@​veggiedefender](https://redirect.github.com/veggiedefender)! - Increase the maxBuffer size for capnp uploads

- [#​10356](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10356) [`80e964c`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/80e964c7c756895719b94c0597da23dca91c2c34) Thanks [@​WillTaylorDev](https://redirect.github.com/WillTaylorDev)! - fix: Update regex for valid branch name to remove 61 char length requirement, allowing for longer branch names to be specified for preview aliases.

- [#​10289](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10289) [`a5a1426`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/a5a1426a9ead85d2518f01fde0c1dbc02f98c4df) Thanks [@​emily-shen](https://redirect.github.com/emily-shen)! - Cleanup container images created during local dev if no changes have been made.

  We now untag old images that were created by Wrangler/Vite if we find that the image content and configuration is unchanged, so that we don't keep accumulating image tags.

- [#​10315](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10315) [`0c04da9`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/0c04da9b3a8dcf1220b46a0fdd463ba0bad0f9a1) Thanks [@​emily-shen](https://redirect.github.com/emily-shen)! - Add `rollout_active_grace_period` option to containers configuration.

  This allows users to configure how long an active container should keep running for during a rollout, before the upgrade is applied.

- [#​10321](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10321) [`b524a6f`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/b524a6fd4a19ef551517bb6c8cb32582862f7202) Thanks [@​emily-shen](https://redirect.github.com/emily-shen)! - print prettier errors during container deployment

- [#​10253](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10253) [`eb32a3a`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/eb32a3ab4c4446a4844bea71353b59e36715e6a6) Thanks [@​emily-shen](https://redirect.github.com/emily-shen)! - fix redeploying container apps when previous deploy failed or container (but not image) was deleted.

  Previously this failed with `No changes detected but no previous image found` as we assumed there would be a previous deployment when an image exists in the registry.

- [#​9990](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/9990) [`4288a61`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/4288a61c1f8abd8243d3218749ea700a383954b9) Thanks [@​penalosa](https://redirect.github.com/penalosa)! - Fix startup profiling when sourcemaps are enabled

- Updated dependencies \[[`d54d8b7`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/d54d8b73a2771cde9645937ff241675dddf0e8d2), [`ae0c806`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/ae0c806087c203da6a3d7da450e8fabe0d81c987)]:
  - miniflare@4.20250813.1

### [`v4.29.1`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/blob/HEAD/packages/wrangler/CHANGELOG.md#4291)

[Compare Source](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/compare/wrangler@4.29.0...wrangler@4.29.1)

##### Patch Changes

- Updated dependencies \[[`5020694`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/5020694dd35578dcf3f1669780889fc0ba632c8e)]:
  - miniflare@4.20250813.0

### [`v4.29.0`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/blob/HEAD/packages/wrangler/CHANGELOG.md#4290)

[Compare Source](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/compare/wrangler@4.28.1...wrangler@4.29.0)

##### Minor Changes

- [#​10283](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10283) [`80960b9`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/80960b9297a8e6009ee19fa8708651539fec76d6) Thanks [@​WillTaylorDev](https://redirect.github.com/WillTaylorDev)! - Support long branch names in generation of branch aliases in WCI.

- [#​10312](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10312) [`bd8223d`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/bd8223de34e74b150a0c7ac5fc66488791f17178) Thanks [@​devin-ai-integration](https://redirect.github.com/apps/devin-ai-integration)! - Added `--domain` flag to `wrangler deploy` command for deploying to custom domains. Use `--domain example.com` to deploy directly to a custom domain without manually configuring routes.

- [#​8318](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/8318) [`8cf47f9`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/8cf47f954d621d20e4dfb3685f7e496792853c51) Thanks [@​gnekich](https://redirect.github.com/gnekich)! - Introduce json output flag for wrangler pages deployment list

##### Patch Changes

- [#​10232](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10232) [`e7cae16`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/e7cae16d5be9a8a0487ffab351ccf8f27808524f) Thanks [@​emily-shen](https://redirect.github.com/emily-shen)! - fix: validate `wrangler containers delete ID` to ensure a valid ID has been provided. Previously if you provided the container name (or any non-ID shaped string) you would get an auth error instead of a 404.

- [#​10139](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10139) [`3b6ab8a`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/3b6ab8a8745367f05f370df163d908560b7e18a6) Thanks [@​dom96](https://redirect.github.com/dom96)! - Removes mention of cf-requirements when Python Workers are enabled

- [#​10259](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10259) [`c58a05c`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/c58a05cdc6d4e900541857be0e931250352199b8) Thanks [@​dario-piotrowicz](https://redirect.github.com/dario-piotrowicz)! - Ensure that `maybeStartOrUpdateRemoteProxySession` considers the potential account\_id from the user's wrangler config

  Currently if the user has an `account_id` in their wrangler config file, such id won't be taken into consideration for the remote proxy session, the changes here make sure that it is (note that the `auth` option of `maybeStartOrUpdateRemoteProxySession`, if provided, takes precedence over this id value).

  The changes here also fix the same issue for `wrangler dev` and `getPlatformProxy` (since they use `maybeStartOrUpdateRemoteProxySession` under the hook).

- [#​10288](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10288) [`42aafa3`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/42aafa3bbea18aa41962610eb5b828790c9a4727) Thanks [@​tgarg-cf](https://redirect.github.com/tgarg-cf)! - Do not attempt to update queue producer settings when deploying a Worker with a queue binding

  Previously, each deployed Worker would update a subset of the queue producer's settings for each queue binding, which could result in broken queue producers or at least conflicts where different Workers tried to set different producer settings on a shared queue.

- [#​10242](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10242) [`70bd966`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/70bd9665fefd33ddf84b84d6938a46f0501eec1a) Thanks [@​devin-ai-integration](https://redirect.github.com/apps/devin-ai-integration)! - Add experimental API to expose Wrangler command tree structure for documentation generation

- [#​10258](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10258) [`d391076`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/d39107694b6bd9d63f15b529798aba0fd9a43643) Thanks [@​nikitassharma](https://redirect.github.com/nikitassharma)! - Add the option to allow all tiers when creating a container

- [#​10248](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10248) [`422ae22`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/422ae22348ca7b4cc394987e547517ae0aae461d) Thanks [@​emily-shen](https://redirect.github.com/emily-shen)! - fix: re-push container images on deploy even if the only change was to the Dockerfile

- [#​10179](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10179) [`5d5ecd5`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/5d5ecd558d58461f203f882011df3e4d2652305c) Thanks [@​pombosilva](https://redirect.github.com/pombosilva)! - Prevent defining multiple workflows with the same "name" property in the same wrangler file

- [#​10232](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10232) [`e7cae16`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/e7cae16d5be9a8a0487ffab351ccf8f27808524f) Thanks [@​emily-shen](https://redirect.github.com/emily-shen)! - include containers API calls in output of WRANGLER\_LOG=debug

- [#​10243](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10243) [`d481901`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/d48190127fbb564c5abdd3c8f33433a6381d8899) Thanks [@​devin-ai-integration](https://redirect.github.com/apps/devin-ai-integration)! - Remove async\_hooks polyfill - now uses native workerd implementation

  The async\_hooks module is now provided natively by workerd, making the polyfill unnecessary. This improves performance and ensures better compatibility with Node.js async\_hooks APIs.

- [#​10060](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10060) [`9aad334`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/9aad334d282c863971b1ee84324ecfc60a022222) Thanks [@​edmundhung](https://redirect.github.com/edmundhung)! - refactor: switch `getPlatformProxy()` to use Miniflare's dev registry implementation

  Updated `getPlatformProxy()` to use Miniflare's dev registry instead of Wrangler's implementation. Previously, you had to start a wrangler or vite dev session before accessing the proxy bindings to connect to those workers. Now the order doesn't matter.

- [#​10219](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/pull/10219) [`28494f4`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/28494f413bba3c509c56762b9260edd0ffef4f28) Thanks [@​dario-piotrowicz](https://redirect.github.com/dario-piotrowicz)! - fix `NonRetryableError` thrown with an empty error message not stopping workflow retries locally

- Updated dependencies \[[`1479fd0`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/1479fd06b91f9ab529ba4b8824d938e5da3184a0), [`05c5b28`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/05c5b286307bb4b55bd7768bd5873b54f8b06079), [`e3d9703`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/e3d9703c8733567b9bcad4d6264958f6ba6876f6), [`d481901`](https://redirect.github.com/cloudflare/workers-sdk/commit/d48190127fbb564c5abdd3c8f33433a6381d8899)]:

issue.title: Prepare for Maven 4

labels.name: needs:triage
labels.description: Requires attention from one of the committers

issue.body:
### Description

The current Apache Maven support in NetBeans is tightly bound to Maven 3.x.y. 

Maven 4 introduces a number of improvements, one of which is a proper API in a separate package/module.
Moving from maven 3.9.x to maven 4 is not trivial, because of the API changes.
The Apache Maven project strives to be backward compatible, in particular with to respect to the supported Maven Model versions.

We that the introduction of a proper Maven API simplifies integration into NetBeans as Maven client application. 

The new integration should :

* Support execution of Maven goals projects based on model versions > 4.0.0
* Support editor hints of a Maven 4 pom.xml file based on model version supported by Maven  4.
* Listening for  and understanding of Maven goal execution events.
* Support Maven 4 features introduced with Maven model version >= 4.1.0

This issue will be used to log advancement in this endeavour.

Several suggestions have been made to move NetBeans forward in this direction.
One is to use the mvnw wrapper as execution vehicle for the time.
This can be based on Mavens [ExecutorTool](https://github.com/apache/maven/blob/master/impl/maven-executor/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/cling/executor/ExecutorTool.java) and [ToolboxTool](https://github.com/apache/maven/blob/master/impl/maven-executor/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/cling/executor/internal/ToolboxTool.java).
These Maven API interfaces may be usable be used to adapt NetBeans [MavenCommandLineExecutor](https://github.com/apache/netbeans/blob/master/java/maven/src/org/netbeans/modules/maven/execute/MavenCommandLineExecutor.java).



### Use case/motivation

To move NetBeans forward.

### Related issues

Issue #8632

### Are you willing to submit a pull request?

Yes, when I have something worth pulling.

Hey! I started working on support for JDA. Still need to finish some stuff up but I wanted to get it here so I can get some feedback.

Currently working on converting the rest of the files (notably button and action row).

I'm also going off of the example provided here: https://github.com/discord-jda/JDA/blob/master/src/examples/java/ComponentsV2Example.java (as well as reading the Javadocs a bit)

comment.body:
I will also note the necessity of a tool to facilitate testing codegen support. One idea is to have a node script which generates all permutations of components, then each contributor wishing to add support for their library must:
1. Make a function taking all permutations as input, then generate all the code, the output format is up to the contributor, for example, in Java, one could create a single text file with each permutation in it's own block (`{ <permutation code> }`) to avoid conflicts
2. Test the generated code compiles
3. (Optionally) Test the generated code works at runtime

It is, however, not a goal to automate these tests, it is only a tool for the contributors themselves, snapshot tests *may* be welcome though, to verify output changes (or doesn't) as expected.

refactor(backend): Change Prompt from record to class and update data access

Refactors the `Prompt` domain object from a Java Record to a Class to support mutability for updates. Adds `conversationId` and `response` fields. The `PromptRepository` is changed to an interface to decouple it from the specific data store, improving flexibility for future storage options.

issue.title: Several inputs lose focus in un-user-friendly ways

labels.name: tea_kettle
labels.description: This issue should be closed before tea_kettle is retired

issue.body:
On the recipe edit page, when you hit enter on the ingredients field, it creates a new ingredient entry, but doesn't focus the input, effectively rendering the desired functionality useless.

When searching recipes, the search box loses focus after a search completes. It should remain focused.

When adding an item to a shopping list, the add box does not maintain focus after the item is added.

issue.body:
Signed-off-by: Igor Bezukh <ibezukh@redhat.com>

Runbook PR: https://github.com/openshift/runbooks/pull/318

**What this PR does / why we need it**:
In an upgrade scenario it can happen that duplicate wasp-agent
deployment can appear, since previous wasp-agent deployments
were manual and in a different namespace.
Therefore in order to make sure the user is aware of it we
are adding an alert which will rely on the a metric of memory
overcommit percentage and presence of wasp namespace.

Helm v3.17.4 is a patch release, this bring is the security release noted below. This is intended for Helm SDK users. CLI users are recommended to use the latest version of Helm.

Updating Hexo from ^5.3.0 to ^7.2.0 skips version 6 entirely, which may introduce breaking changes. Ensure this major version update is compatible with the existing hexo plugins and configuration.
```suggestion
    "hexo": "^5.3.0",
```

- Add proper TypeScript support and error handling

Updating react-scripts from 3.3.0 to 5.0.0 is a major version jump that may introduce breaking changes. Ensure this update is compatible with the existing React 16.12.0 version, as React Scripts 5.0.0 typically requires React 17 or higher.
```suggestion
    "react-scripts": "4.0.3",
```

issue.title: Fix ESLint React Hook dependency warnings in useEffect
issue.body:
Fixed ESLint React Hook dependency warnings that were causing CI failures on the copilot/fix-19 branch. The warnings were related to missing dependencies in `useEffect` hooks used for the rest timer functionality.

## Issues Fixed

**1. Missing dependencies in timer useEffect**
The timer effect was using `state.restTimer.startTime` and `state.restTimer.totalTime` inside the effect but not including them in the dependency array:

```javascript
useEffect(() => {
  // Uses startTime and totalTime but they weren't in dependencies
  const elapsedSeconds = Math.floor((now - state.restTimer.startTime) / 1000);
  const newTimeLeft = Math.max(0, state.restTimer.totalTime - elapsedSeconds);
}, [state.restTimer.isActive, state.restTimer.timeLeft]); // Missing startTime, totalTime
```

**2. Missing function dependency in notification useEffect**
The notification effect was calling `showRestCompleteNotification()` but not including it in the dependency array, which could lead to stale closures.

## Solution

- Added `useCallback` import from React
- Wrapped `showRestCompleteNotification` with `useCallback` to memoize the function and prevent unnecessary re-renders
- Added missing state dependencies to the timer useEffect dependency array
- Added the memoized function to the notification useEffect dependency array

The changes ensure proper React Hook dependency management while maintaining the exact same timer functionality. ESLint now passes without warnings, and the rest timer continues to work correctly for strength and hypertrophy workouts.

![Working app interface](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0725796c-ad43-48c6-bf4d-d5bca6f46a1c)

Fixes #22.

issue.title: Revert usage of excessively new Kirigami API
issue.body:
This change depends on
https://invent.kde.org/frameworks/kirigami/-/merge_requests/1795, which is released, but the Frameworks version containing it isn't yet in the KDE Runtime. We missed this at build-time because the Frameworks dependency version was not updated in CMake when the merge request was merged for NeoChat.

Fixes https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=508298

However, the actual changes shown in the diff are primarily Python code formatting updates (converting single quotes to double quotes and organizing imports) along with a few minor package version updates. - Updates @redwoodjs/api dependency to fix security vulnerabilities - Standardizes Python code formatting across test fixtures (single to double quotes) - Updates several package dependencies to newer versions ### Reviewed Changes Copilot reviewed 51 out of 56 changed files in this pull request and generated 3 comments.

pull_request.body:
## Summary
- add `models_pull_runpod.sh` to fetch and cache models then sync to Drive
- add ModelsCache check in `warm` target and new `models_pull_runpod` target
- whitelist Airwindows/Dragonfly LV2 URIs and escape OUT_BASENAME in main.nf
- document first-run model pull for RunPod

## Testing
- `bash scripts/verify_lv2_uris.sh` *(fails: LV2 map not found)*
- `python3 scripts/final_repo_gate.py`

performed_via_github_app.description:
Codecov provides highly integrated tools to group, merge, archive and compare coverage reports. Whether your team is comparing changes in a pull request or reviewing a single commit, Codecov will improve the code review workflow and quality.

## Code coverage done right.®

1. Upload coverage reports from your CI builds.
2. Codecov merges all builds and languages into one beautiful coherent report.
3. Get commit statuses, pull request comments and coverage overlay via our browser extension.

When Codecov merges your uploads it keeps track of the CI provider (inc. build details) and user specified context, e.g. `#unittest` ~ `#smoketest` or `#oldcode` ~ `#newcode`. You can track the `#unittest` coverage independently of other groups. [Learn more here](
http://docs.codecov.io/docs/flags)

Through **Codecov's Browser Extension** reports overlay directly in GitHub UI to assist in code review in [Chrome](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/codecov/gedikamndpbemklijjkncpnolildpbgo) or Firefox (https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/codecov/)

*Highly detailed* **pull request comments** and *customizable* **commit statuses** will improve your team's workflow and code coverage incrementally.

**File backed configuration** all through the `codecov.yml`. 

## FAQ
- Do you **merge multiple uploads** to the same commit? **Yes**
- Do you **support multiple languages** in the same project? **Yes**
- Can you **group coverage reports** by project and/or test type? **Yes**
- How does **pricing** work? Only paid users can view reports and post statuses/comments.

issue.title: [Snyk] Fix for 11 vulnerabilities
issue.body:
![snyk-top-banner](https://github.com/andygongea/OWASP-Benchmark/assets/818805/c518c423-16fe-447e-b67f-ad5a49b5d123) ### Snyk has created this PR to fix 11 vulnerabilities in the yarn dependencies of this project. #### Snyk changed the following file(s): - `examples/brunch/package.json` #### Note for [zero-installs](https://yarnpkg.com/features/zero-installs) users If you are using the Yarn feature [zero-installs](https://yarnpkg.com/features/zero-installs) that was introduced in Yarn V2, note that this PR does not update the `.yarn/cache/` directory meaning this code cannot be pulled and immediately developed on as one would expect for a zero-install project - you will need to run `yarn` to update the contents of the `./yarn/cache` directory. If you are not using zero-install you can ignore this as your flow should likely be unchanged.

chore: v4.0.3 unify factory and remove legacy
Update the version of tinystruct framework.

Major AI Toolbox enhancement and Spirit Chat improvements

- Add comprehensive file management AI tools for Spirits
  * New tools: listFiles, getFileContent, createDirectory, updateFileEfficient, getProjectTree, manageFile
  * AI Tool management: listAITools, setAIToolActive for self-management
  * Remove deprecated updateUserProfile tool
  * Migration Version20250812191800 with smart active/inactive defaults

- Implement AIToolToolService for meta-tool management
  * Allows Spirits to manage their own toolset
  * List available tools with filtering
  * Toggle tool activation/deactivation
  * Safety checks to prevent disabling core tools

- Enhance Spirit Chat system
  * Improved API service and manager components
  * Better UI styling and responsiveness
  * Enhanced conversation flow and user experience

- Update service architecture
  * Enhanced AIToolCallService with new tool integrations
  * Improved file service capabilities
  * Better gateway service implementations
  * Updated service container configuration

- Expand internationalization
  * Complete translations for new AI tools (en, cs, sk)
  * Enhanced user settings and AI configuration pages
  * Improved Spirit Chat interface translations

- Documentation updates
  * Updated README with comprehensive project overview
  * Enhanced setup instructions and feature descriptions
  * Improved development guidelines and architecture docs
